text.tspan: External user or service sends a request
to validate an API key.
Applies rate limiting to prevent abuse.
Limits requests to 100 per minute per IP.

g.text: Forwards the request to the internal API engine.

text.tspan: User requests to publish a new API key
for a specific item with defined permissions.
Generates a random 64-character API key
using a secure random generator.
Hashes the generated API key using
Argon2id for secure storage.
Stores the hashed API key along with
its metadata in the database.
Checks for duplicates before storing.

g.text: User requests to validate an API key.

text.tspan: Locks the API key validation process
using a distributed lock to prevent
race conditions.

g.text: First checks the cache for the hashed API key.
If not found in cache, fetches from the database.

text.tspan: Verifies the provided API key against the hashed key
using Argon2id.
If valid, checks expiration and usage limits.
If valid, increments the usage count
and updates the cache.
